'''Michiel Hendrik de Kock''' (29 January 1898, [[Malmesbury, Western Cape]] —18 September 1976, [[Cape Town]]) was the third Governor of the [[South African Reserve Bank]]. His term of office was from 1 July 1945 to 30 June 1962.<ref name="ResBank">{{cite web | url=http://www.resbank.co.za/AboutUs/History/PreviousGovernors/Pages/DrMichielHendrikdeKock.aspx | title=Previous Governors | accessdate=2013-04-11}}</ref> All South African [[banknote]]s issued during the reign of [[Elizabeth II of the United Kingdom|Queen Elizabeth II]] carry his signature. The [[Union of South Africa]] became the [[Republic of South Africa]] under the Constitution of the First Republic on 31 May 1961. His signature is also carried on the first issue of [[South African rand|Rand]] banknotes, which were first issued on 14 February 1961. His successor was Dr. [[G. Rissik]]. His son, Dr. [[G.P.C. de Kock]] also served as a Governor of the South African Reserve Bank.

