{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2018}} {{Use Indian English|date=October 2018}} {{Infobox company |name = Trivandrum Rubber Works |logo = |type = |foundation = 1963 |location_city = [[Thiruvananthapuram]] |location_country = [[India]] |key_people = |num_employees = 163 (As on 2005) |industry = [[Manufacturing]] |products = Tread rubber, Cycle tyres, etc. |revenue = |location = |locations = |area_served = |services = |parent = |divisions = |subsid = |dissolved = |footnotes = |operating_income = |net_income = |homepage = }}
'''Trivandrum Rubber Works''' is a [[Public sector undertakings in Kerala|public sector]] manufacturing industry in [[Thiruvananthapuram]], [[Kerala]], [[India]].<ref>{{cite book|last=Pillai|first=V. Gangadharan|title=The public sector in Kerala: administrative problems|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Kp4EAAAAMAAJ&q=%22Trivandrum+Rubber+Works%22&dq=%22Trivandrum+Rubber+Works%22&hl=en&ei=Y7z3S_uONoSyrAfu8fmwCg&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=1&ved=0CCwQ6AEwAA|year=1980}}</ref> Its manufactured products include, retreaded metals, bonding gum and unvulcanised sheets.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bpe.kerala.gov.in/pages/BPE%20Doc/66.pdf|title=TRIVANDRUM RUBBER WORKS LIMITED|publisher=BPE Planning & Economic Affairs Department, [[Government of Kerala]]|accessdate=22 May 2010}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|title=Modern Technology of Rubber and Allied Industries|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=dyPxF2JHtzoC&pg=PA496&dq=%22Trivandrum+Rubber+Works%22&hl=en&ei=Y7z3S_uONoSyrAfu8fmwCg&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=8&ved=0CEgQ6AEwBw#v=onepage&q=%22Trivandrum%20Rubber%20Works%22&f=false|publisher=National Institute of Industrial Research, [[New Delhi]]}}</ref> It was promoted by [[Kerala State Industrial Development Corporation|Kerala State Industrial Development Corporation (KSIDC)]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ksidc.org/KSIDC-assisted-units.php |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2010-05-22 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100326091255/http://www.ksidc.org/KSIDC-assisted-units.php |archivedate=2010-03-26 |df= }}</ref>
==History== The factory was opened by [[Sree Chithira Thirunal Balarama Varma]], the then King of [[Travancore|Travancore Kingdom]], to manufacture rubber sheets for tents for the soldiers of the [[Second World War]].<ref name="hindu_jan06">{{cite news|url=http://www.hindu.com/2006/01/25/stories/2006012508330400.htm|title=Trivandrum Rubber Works on the verge of closure|date=25 January 2006|publisher=[[The Hindu]]|accessdate=22 May 2010}}</ref> It is located on {{convert|13.28|acre|m2}} of land at [[Chakkai]], [[Thiruvananthapuram]].
Trivandrum Rubber Works was the first factory to be set up in the [[public sector]] in [[Asia]].<ref name="hindu_jan06" />
