'''Vui Florence Tuaumu Saulo''' is a businesswoman and politician from American Samoa.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|url=http://www.pacwip.org/resources/news/2012/vui-florence-saulo-only-woman-in-new-house-american-samoa.html|title=Pacific Women in Politics|website=Pacific Women in Politics|access-date=2017-11-30}}</ref>
Saulo founded her own finance and insurance company and in November 2012 she was elected to the House of Representatives of American Samoa, to represent Tualauta County.<ref name=":0" /> She was the only woman in the House, although in 2014 a second woman, [[Atalina Asifoa]], was elected and for two years there were two women in the legislature.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://samoanews.com/local-news/once-again-tualauta-faipule-vui-only-woman-fono|title=Once again Tualauta faipule Vui is the only woman in the Fono {{!}} Samoa News|website=samoanews.com|language=en|access-date=2017-11-30}}</ref>
After Saulo's election in 2012 her eligibility to stand was challenged on the grounds that she had allegedly not been required to provide a birth certificate in order to register as a candidate in the election.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.radionz.co.nz/international/pacific-news/208687/electoral-challenge-against-only-woman-elected-to-american-samoa-house|title=Electoral challenge against only woman elected to American Samoa House|date=2012-11-23|work=Radio New Zealand|access-date=2017-11-30|language=en-nz}}</ref>
